Team

Ujjwal Upadhyay
Team Lead

Mr Upadhyay has been working in CREASION since March 2024 as Team Leader of the Project Collaborative Approach for Preventing Plastic Leakages in Rivers of Nepal (CAP). Mr Ujjwal Upadhyay is a prominently skilled expert, manager, director and trainer working in the field of climate change impact, adaptation and mitigation, environment impact assessment, disaster risk reduction, sustainable development, circular economy, conservation, livelihood, transboundary water resources management, and education. Ujjwal has substantially devoted his career in sustainable development in an international context, focusing on development issues linked to environmental risk mitigation, climate adaptation, water management, landscapes, conservation and the society, including how communities can sustainably manage natural resources while working for increased resilience amid many environmental challenges. Having worked with various international organizations like ICIMOD, WWF, OXFAM, USAID, UNDP, UNEP, CICERO, VSO, ADB, Dan Church Aid, Finn Church Aid, Konrad Adenauer Stiftung,(KAS), RESTLESS DEVELOPMENT, The World Bank along with various international universities in Japan, Thailand, Europe and US including government organizations, Ujjwal has contributed to numerous policies and projects and have also published research papers and articles in prominent journals and books of international standards.

Anjali Mehta
Training and Capacity building officer

Ms. Mehta is appointed as Training and Capacity building officer for Project CAP (Collaborative Approach for Preventing Plastic Leakages in Rivers). She holds a Bachelor's degree in Mechanical Engineering from Nitte Meenakshi Institute of Technology in Bangalore. Her passion to study and impart what she has learned has always motivated her. She has worked in a variety of diverse disciplines, including technical, business, management, and education, as a result of her interest. She loves dogs and enjoys engaging in conversations about feminism and gender responsibility & issues.

Prabin Bhandari
Infra-Coordinator

Mr. Prabin is a graduate Mechanical Engineer resident of Nawalparasi, currently living in Kathmandu. He is pursuing his master degree in Energy Systems under department of Global Engagement from Indian Institute of Technology Madras, Chennai. He has experience in Mechanical scope of works in Hydropower Project, Solar Power Project and Construction related works. He is youth activist on catastrophic climate change issue that have impact on society. He is also a member of Raleigh Nepal. He loves nature and adventure like hiking.

Palistha Manandhar
Project Associate

Palistha serves as a Project Associate for Project CAP (Collaborative Approach for Preventing Plastic Leakages in Rivers). She holds a bachelor’s degree in Environmental Engineering from Kathmandu University. She is deeply committed to environmental sustainability and impactful green projects. She has worked across diverse aspects of health and climate initiatives, and has actively contributed to projects in waste management, WASH, and climate change. Currently, she is pursuing MBA to enhance her technical skills with a management perspective, reflecting a dedication to comprehensive project leadership.

Larisha Dhakal
MERL Officer

Ms. Larisha serves as a Monitoring, Evaluation, Research, and Learning (MERL) Officer at CREASION, spearheading efforts to establish an efficient MERL system for projects led by CREASION. She holds a Master’s Degree in Urban Economic Development from University College London, where she acquired theoretical knowledge and practical approaches related to fostering productive, sustainable, and inclusive urban and local economies. Her dissertation delved into the assessment of the effectiveness of Public-Private Partnerships (PPP) for solid waste management in Kathmandu Metropolis, employing an institutional lens. Previously, she worked as an economic consultant at Metro Dynamics, contributing to various projects centred around local economic development and inclusive growth in the UK. Furthermore, she has been involved in initiatives supporting innovation in Nepal, such as the Nepal Innovation Challenge - AgriTech by UNCDF, NEXT Launchpad, and Udhyami Seedcamp.

Shyam Subedi
Sr. Finance Officer

Shyam Subedi is the Senior Finance and Administrative Officer whose core interest lies in finances and the economy. He has been working in the development sector for more than a decade. He is an alumni of Nepal Mega College where he studied Masters in Business Studies. He is an enthusiastic learner and has a passion in mathematics. Besides, having an interest in the financial sector, he is an adventure lover who loves to hike and do various outdoor activities.
